They are able to cope with the challenges of life. They can keep problems in perspective and bounce back from setbacks. They feel good about themselves and have healthy relationships. Being emotionally healthy does not mean that you are happy all the time. It means that you are aware of your emotions. You can deal with them, whether they are positive or negative. Emotionally healthy people also experience stress, anger, and sadness. But they know how to handle their negative feelings. They can know when a problem is more than they can handle alone.
